Inheritance:
1. Code Reusability: Child class can make use of parent class's fields and methods
2. Run Time Polymorphism: Method Overriding (methodA is available in parent class - but the child class want it lil different -
hence the child class decide to provide a new definition).
3. Abstract Classes 

		Polygon
1.Rectangle 2.Square

The keyword is always used to call parent class's methods and constructors.

